==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Public school
<hw>Public school</hw>. <sd>(a)</sd> <def>In Great Britain, any of
various schools maintained by the community, wholly or partly under
public control, or maintained largely by endowment and not carried on
chiefly for profit; specif., and commonly, any of various select and
usually expensive endowed schools which give a liberal modern education
or prepare pupils for the universities. Eton, Harrow, Rugby, and
Winchester are of this class.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>In the United
States, a free primary, grammar, or high school maintained by the local
government.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Quasi-public corporation</ent>⟦br⟧
